The paper deals with the problem of handling image resolution variations in person re-identification, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves deep learning techniques and a novel objective function, which suggests that it could also fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves experiments and evaluations, which could place it under multimedia (cs.MM) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of learning from images with different resolutions, which could also place it under information retrieval (cs.IR).
